cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.CY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is the most likely category as the paper deals with recommender systems and matching items based on user preferences. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel method for learning pairwise similarity in attribute space. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is relevant as the paper considers user preferences and tastes in consuming content. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is relevant as the paper deals with natural language processing in identifying matching items. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is less likely but still possible as the paper considers user behavior and preferences in consuming content, which has societal implications.
